Attack On Frightside
A Neo Scary God-Game

by Farley Sweet

You are in a Cell.
You can see a Cell Door.
You can go out.
You're locked inside a dark cell and there isn't much space. The smell of feces is strong. The air is thick. Besides the sound of water dripping you can hear faint thumps from the outside world.

Your head is sore and you can't quite remember how you ended up here. For now it doesn't matter--you just want to leave.

The cell door in front of you might be locked but it sure is rusted. You wonder if you can kick it down and get out of here.

> kick cell door

> kick cell door
The cell door breaks off of its hinges and falls to the ground.
> out

> out

You are in a Stairwell.
You can go up.
Exiting your filthy cell you stumble into a dim, but oddly warm, stairwell. Your head still has an ache to it but that won't stop you from getting up the stairs.

> up

> up

You are in a Firey Grove.
You can go north.
You've entered a grove of some kind--or what used to be one as this one was currently on fire! The flames lit up the night sky above you and seemed to be quickly spreading to the stone structure that you just escaped!

What scared you more than the flames however was the booming voice that greeted you, "Do you fear the monsters, mortal?"

You look up and see a young, blonde haired man standing on top of a horned devil statue--in fact, the young man has a pair of his own horns as well!

Before you ask what's going on the man spoke again, "You may have escaped but that doesn't make you are any less of a prisoner to me. Why, getting out before the smoke got you probably worked out for the best anyway."

A glowing ball of engery was just then lauched at the devilish man. He jumped out of harm's way at the last second, leaving the statue below him to explode. The source of the engery attack ran right by your side--a little girl?

"Stranger, I don't know who you are but if Jimmy's got a beef with you then you must be good," the little girl, dressed in what looked like a fairy costume, said. "We need to get out of here!"

The devilish man, 'Jimmy', struck a menacing pose towards you, "Fool! I shall take my leave now but do not think you will survive the night!" His dark eyes shifted to the girl beside you, "Hannah! It's useless--USELESS, USELESS, USELESS!"

And with that the bizarre Jimmy lept back into the burning grove and out of sight.

"He's gone. Let's move out," the little girl, 'Hannah', ordered.

You have no clue what's going on but the girl is right.
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE ALREADY!

> n

> n
Trees collapse behind you and Hannah as you flee from the grove and out of the forest. You feel relief as the smokey terror chasing you fades away.

You are in a Clearing.
You can see a Grove and a Spooky House.
You can go east.
Finally feeling a sense of safety, you catch your breath along with Hannah.

"I'm glad you're okay. Sounds like Jimmy had something nasty planned for you," said Hannah. "My name is Hannah Urameshi by the way. I don't know who you are or what your story is but listen--I was really relying on my engery blast back there to take Jimmy by surprise. Well, you saw him dodge it and now I really don't have the willpower to summon that much power back. Jimmy needs to be stopped and he needs to be stopped tonight. I need your help to do that. We can talk more about it in a bit. See that house over there? That's Scary Godmother's house--she's friendly and you can rest there as long as you need to."

> e

> e
What a Terrible Night to Have Autism.

You are in a Backyard.
You can go in.
You reach the backyard of the spooky Scary Godmother's house and as if on cue floated out the Godmother herself.
She looked like your run of the mill witch--maybe a little hotter than what you're used to--but when she comes to greet you the bandages and bruises on her body become clear. She's recently seen some battles and they've really left a mark. No doubt this Jimmy fellow is to blame.

"Hannah!" The witch happily cried, "You're still alive!"

Hannah and Scary Godmother exchanged hugs, "I'm glad to see you too, Scary Godmother," said Hannah. "This is my new friend."

Scary Godmother circles you, looking you up and down, "I see. Will your friend be able to put a stop to Jimmy for good?"

"Absolutely! We'll have saved Frightside by morning with the extra help," Hannah cheered.

Scary Godmother nodded her head, "I hope so. Come daybreak Jimmy's curse on Frightside will have reached fullpower and destroy us all if nothing's done soon. But I have faith he can be stopped by then." Scary Godmother smiles at you and gestures you to come insider her home, "Friend, the best party house in all of Frightside is open to you! You can use my home as an HQ. So come back if you ever get stuck in a jam. You'll be greeted as a friend."

> in

> in
Your quest to stop Jimmy has begun.

You are in a Living Room.
You can see Hannah, Scary Godmother and a Doll.
You can go north, east, up or south.
You are standing inside a decorative living room furnished with several comfy chairs and couches. On the walls are paintings of happy halloween characters and glass cases of rare pieces of candy. Above a dresser hangs a flag striped in orange, purple, black, and so on.

You feel safe and secure here--you're not alone. Hannah and Scary Godmother are nearby in the event of any sudden attack.

> speak to hannah

> speak to hannah
"Jimmy is hiding in his dark tower across the bridge. To reach him, you're going to have to climb all the way up there."
> speak to scary godmother

> speak to scary godmother
"Be careful out there. Jimmy's attack on Frightside has already caused much trouble. He'll have his minions, or 'Jimmies', out and about and you're going to want to avoid them if you can."
