You are in a Graveyard.
You can see a Robbed Grave and a Candle Lit Grave.
You can go north, west or east.
Mist creeps by your feet and an unsettling chill flows throughout the area. Gravestone after gravestone surrounds you with Scary Godmother's house in one direction and Jimmy's Tower in the opposite.

A shriek echoes out from an unknown location. You are reminded that you aren't safe out here--and neither is the person who just cried out.
> w

> w
You catch the smell of blood sneak by your nose and hear yet another painful shriek--this time it's quite close!

You are by a Lone Tree.
You can see Daryl and a Neko.
You can go east or northwest.
A lone, dying tree is found near the edge of the graveyard. From the tree hangs a terrible sight.

You creep down and hide behind a grave. In front of you are three people--and a fourth one hanging from the tree! A young girl dressed in black, wearing furry cat ears over her head, is pushed down by a deformed thug sporting a grey trenchcoat and a bright green shirt. Next to the greasy thug is a tan body builder with lush purple hair and a "I would die for Jimmy" tattoo across his chest. These two are Jimmies!

"How could you kill my beloved Daryl?" Cried the girl before the greasy thug kicked her face.

"QUIED! If iets for Muster Jummy anyting goe," the greasy thug coughed.

The other Jimmie stepped forward, "Back off Aigee PeAitch, I, the loyal Chocolate Magma, shall deliver the final blow on behalf of Lord Jimmy."

And with that the girl's neck was snapped under the large Jimmie's foot. Chocolate Magma sniffed the air--you worry he caught your scent--but as soon as Aigee PeAitch farted he ceased sniffing and took his leave with his fellow Jimmie.

Now you understand what horror Jimmy has brought to Frightside.

