You are on a Bridge.
You can go east or west.
The bridge is made of cobblestone and leads right up to Jimmy's Tower! Below you is a dark cliff that you don't want to see the bottom of.

As you begin to cross the bridge an anorexic man in rags, wearing a turtle shell as a helmet, moves in front of you. He aims his spear at you and growls, "You will not cross this bridge! You will die for Lord Jimmy!"

Jumping up from the depths of the canyon is a large blue monster! "You pesky Jimmies are really giving me a headache!"

The monster turns his back to you, grabs the Jimmie, and throws him over the side. His squeal echoes throughout Frightside while the monster moves forward.

> w

> w

You at the a Tower Gate.
You can see a Monster.
You can go east or in.
You are standing at the entrance of Jimmy's Tower. Horned skulls are a common design on the tower, now that you can see it up close.

Resting by the closed gate is the blue monster. He has several yellow eyes and two sharp horns. He looks hurt and is breathing heavy.

"Hey, kid," the monster says to you, "The way is locked from the inside. We gotta break the damn gate down. I would gladly knock the gate down myself but I'm all out of energy after my battle with that purple haired fruit, watz-his-face. Right now I need your help. Find me something to restore my energy and we can put an end to this nightmare!"
> speak to monster

> speak to monster
"Falling into that canyon can really hurt! I don't think that Jimmie I tossed down there will have a soft landing though, Bwah hah!"
> give jar of milk to monster

> give jar of milk to monster
"Thanks kid!" The monster takes the jar of milk and gulps it down. "Woah I feel great. Alright, I'm ready now!" The monster takes a deep breath and barges into the gate--knocking it down. "The way's open. Lead the way, kid."
> in

> in
Thunder erupts once again as you and the monster enter Jimmy's Tower. However, once you enter there is a flash dropping off someone in the center.

You are in a Main Hall.
You can see Chocolate Magma and Bug a boo.
You can go up.

You see a strong looking man with purple hair--it's Chocolate Magma!

"How dare you break into Lord Jimmy's home!" Chocolate Magma looks over to the monster and names him in disgusted shock, "BUG-A-BOO!?"

Bug-a-boo laughs, "Miss me? I'm feeling better now so I'm ready for a rematch, Magma."

"Rematch?" Chocolate Magma looks furious! "I, the fabulous Chocolate Magma, threw you into the canyon! You should be dead!"

Bug-a-boo moves in front of you, "No. You should be."

Bug-a-boo and Chocolate Magma circle each other, you take cover behind a piller, and a cool beat starts playing out of nowhere. With the beat, Bug-a-boo begins to lay a sweet rap down! "This is Bug-a-boo, I'm here forever--And I’m never going down at the hands of the likes of you; Because I’m so much better!"

Chocolate Magma flings a bolt of dark energy at Bug-a-boo. The blue monster jumps out of the way but the bolt destroys the bridge--there's no going back now.

The two began to fight and exchanged blow after blow! Bug-a-boo never stopped singing and after every hit he took he delivered a slash of his own. They smashed each other into the walls and through the pillers but as Bug-a-boo finished his jam he opened his mouth wide and bit down on Chocolate Magma's head. There came a terrible crunch and swallow--Chocolate Magma's body fell back defeated.

Bug-a-boo, wounded, sat back down, "Damn, what a rush. Hey, Kid! That was everything I had so I guess I saved Jimmy for yah. Hurry, the night's almost over!"

> speak to bug a boo

> speak to bug a boo
"Let me tell yah, kid, he did NOT taste like chocolate."
> up

> up
"Give'em hell, kid!" Bug-a-boo shouts. "Purge every last Jimmie you find!"

You are in a Lower Layer.
You can see a Furnace and a Candy.
You can go up.
It appears you're in some kind of candy manufactury. Although, the candy looks and smells cheap and salty. Near the entrance, a furnace burns angirly.

An ape like man with a half melted face quickly hunches over towards you. He smells like--"Shit! You like it!? You eat it!?" The Jimmie-Ape extends his hand out to you as he gets closer. From his hand drips mushy feces, "You like The Scat Fetish, yes? You embrace it!? Come! Embrace it!"

When he reaches you your feet flash to the side away from him. Then! In a poetic twist that not even Shakespeare could come up with, the feces dripped from the ape's hand and onto the floor causing him to step on it and slip! The Jimmie-Ape fell over and into the furnace--melting the remainder of his face and everything else attached to him.

You sigh as he screams. You're ready to be done with this forsaken place.

> up

> up

You are in a Middle Layer.
You can see a Fat Jimmie.
You can go up.
There are many shut windows and even canons in the area. It's likely this layer fired many of the war's first shots. One window, however, is wide open.

A fat Jimmie is standing at the opened window--his body bent into it. He's focused on whatever it is he's doing. He doesn't seem to have noticed your presence.
> push fat jimmie

> push fat jimmie
The fat Jimmie falls over and descends down into the darkness. You can hear his echoey cry as he falls, "YOOOOOOOUUUUUUUUUUUUU!"
> up

> up

You are in a Higher Layer.
You can see Aigee PeAitch.
You can go up.
The room you're in reeks of crayons and spoiled milk. Papers and paint brushes are scattered all over the floor.

At a table, finger painting, is Aigee PeAitch--with his back towards you no less! Looks like you'll be able to decide how to end your feud with him.
> mercy aigee peaitch

> mercy aigee peaitch
You slam your fist on his art table making him jump.

"Yoo! Ward yoo doping her! Plead nah! I den men et!" Aigee PeAitch looks afraid but you flick your eyes onto the door out and back onto him. He gets the message, "I ie tank yoo! THANCH YOO! Ill turn selv en yoo seed!" Aigee PeAitch backs away on his knees, kissing the floor as grows farther and farther away from you. "Tankk yio," he croaks a final time before running away.

Aigee PeAitch has submitted to your command. Victory is yours.
> up

> up
Thunder starts to rumble continuously outside. The reek of crayon is soon replaced with the stench of death. A shiver shoots down your spine.

You are in a Throne Room.
You can see Jimmy.

There! On a dark altar, half submerged into the shadows, stands Jimmy! "Do yoy fear the monsters, mortal!?" The blonde haired demon flicks his hand out and a blast of fire comes right at you! You roll to the side, the fire lighting up the room. With the room visible now you can see Hannah chained against the far wall. Jimmy paces over to her, "Ah, yes. She thought she could sneak through the forest without my notice. I knew YOU were there as well but only now do I see you for the threat that you are."

"Don't worry about me!" Hannah cries out. "Focus on subdu--"

Jimmy snaps his fingers and a rag magically burns around Hannah's mouth, "So noisey." You stare Jimmy down with rage. "Oh? You wish to fight me, is that it? Well it's already over! I can feel the sun's rise! It is nigh! Soon Halloween will end forever, along with this miserable world! The curse I've placed on this world is linked to my very heart." Looks like there'll be no reasoning with Jimmy.

You pose confidently.

"Hmp. I didn't expect you to live this long or be so reckless--but, as I've said before YOU SHALL NOT SURVIVE THE NIGHT!"

What will you do to end the nightmare?
> hug jimmy

> hug jimmy
You approach Jimmy. He only glares at you, waiting for you to attack--but you have something more unconventional in mind.

"What's your game? Why are you moving so slowly--" Jimmy stops speaking as you tenderly wrap your arms around him and hug him tightly.

"Wh-what," Jimmy blushes, frozen in shock. You rest your face beside his arm. "Ah, what are y-you do-doing?"

A single tear rolls down Jimmy's cheek, "H-have I forgotten the feel of human warmth and affection? It's been so long...so, so long." Hesitantly, Jimmy wraps his arms around you. A moment later his body begins to glow! "I brought so much pain to an already wounded world--I-I RENOUNCE IT ALL! SCARY GODMOTHER! HANNAH! I RENOUNCE IT ALL!"

Jimmy's body began to heat up, forcing you to release him. Jimmy floated a few inches off of the ground while you ran to free Hannah. Then! Jimmy's body began to inflate as the Arch Angel Elliot Rodger floated down from the ceiling and offered the agonaized soul of Jimmy his hand. The tower then began to shake!

Hannah freed her mouth, "The dark energy holding this tower together is weakening! This tower is going down! Let's go!"

As you move to the door you can see Hannah looking back and Jimmy one last time with teary eyes. You're not sure what's quite going on but you see the danger and pick up Hannah and run back down the tower.

You make your way down the Middle Layer of the shaking tower when Scary Godmother flies in from an open window, "Get on, quick!" You and Hannah jump onto her magical broom and fly off!

You are in a Field.

The top of Jimmy's Tower explodes and the rest of it falls into the canyon.

Scary Godmother lands and you jump off with Hannah, "You did it," the witch smiles, "you saved Frightside."

The sun rises over the distant mountains--Frightside is truly saved. The nightmare is over.

Hannah gives you a hug of your own, "I knew you could do it. I wish it didn't have to end this way for Jimmy--we were family once. I wish a lot of things here didn't happen. But I'm at least glad to have met you! Frightside is forever in your debt!" Hannah looks to where the dark tower once stood, "But...what about Bug--"

Hearing the start of his name, Bug-a-boo climbed up from the canyon and smiled, "I fell down there once. What's it again plus a tower over my head! Oh yeah--kid, you did good up there."

Scary Godmother gives you a purple and orange card, "This Halloween might have had a lot of...death--BUT come by anytime and we'll party in your honor and in the memories of all our friends!"

You smile and accept the card. You look to the sunrise and reflect on the power a hug can have on a hurt soul.

You have become a true Scary God-Hero.

FIN

